  <span id="freeText17381888181735572781" style="display:none">One of the best resources on first-century history I've had the privilege to enjoy. <br /><br />First, the book is ascetically gorgeous, the size of a coffee table book, the read is visually stunning and I love it. Second, it is wonderfully easy to read; although, the chapters are long, they read very well. Third, all of the footnotes and side articles (even the captions to the photos!) are a "cannot miss" opportunity.<br /><br />All of this should certainly not suggest that the book is shallow or "light" in its content. It had an unbelievably dense amount of academic and scholarly material and the bibliography is fantastic. I was shocked at how it was able to present such a thorough look at the history.<br /><br />I cannot wait to read the next couple volumes! </span>
